# Workflow — versions, CHANGELOG, and release notes

## Canonical version

- **`backend/pyproject.toml`** → `[project].version` is the **single source of truth** for the package.
- Keep the **root `README.md`** product version line in sync when bumping a release (today’s README often uses the Russian label `` `**Версия:**` `` plus `` `v…` ``; use English labels if you translate the README). Full sync checklist: **`version-bump-and-readme.mdc`** / skill **`leap-version-bump`**.

## CHANGELOG (`backend/docs/CHANGELOG.md`)

Add entries for **user-visible behavior**, **API contract** changes, **DB migrations**, **deployment prerequisites**, and **breaking changes**.

### Structure (match existing file)

1. **Release block** (when shipping a version tag):
   - `## vX.Y.Z (YYYY-MM-DD)`
   - Short release summary line (existing entries often use the Russian prefix `` `Релиз:` ``)
   - Optional pointer to dated sections below

2. **Dated feature/fix sections** (preferred for detailed work):
   - `## YYYY-MM-DD: Short English title`
   - Bullets: **bold lead-in** — explanation (REST paths, status codes, env vars **names only**).
   - Subsection `` `### Файлы` `` or `` `### Files` ``: bullet list of **repo-relative paths** touched (match the language used in nearby CHANGELOG entries).

3. **Deploy / ordering notes** when migrations and code must roll out together (see existing Jinja/migration examples).

### Language

- Existing CHANGELOG mixes **Russian** and technical English; **stay consistent with surrounding entries** in the same release. Prefer clear, scannable bullets either way.

### What not to put in CHANGELOG

- Purely internal refactors with no observable effect.
- Secret values or customer data.

## Documentation cross-updates

When you change behavior, update **at least one** of:

| Change type | Update |
|-------------|--------|
| REST API surface | `backend/docs/TECHNICAL.md`, OpenAPI via code |
| Auth / OAuth / creds | `backend/docs/guides/OAUTH.md`, `backend/docs/guides/CREDENTIAL_SECURITY.md` |
| Celery / workers / queues | `backend/docs/guides/CELERY_*.md`, `backend/docs/guides/AUTOMATION_CELERY_BEAT.md` |
| Templates / Jinja metadata | `backend/docs/guides/JINJA_METADATA_TEMPLATES.md` |
| Deployment / env vars | `backend/docs/guides/DEPLOYMENT.md`, `.env.example` |

Keep **`backend/docs/INDEX.md`** accurate if you add new top-level guides.

## Database migrations

- Authoring, numbering, apply/verify: **`alembic-migrations.mdc`**.
- CHANGELOG must mention revision id(s) and **upgrade cautions** (irreversible data migrations, required order vs code deploy).

## Architecture decisions

- Significant design choices → new or updated entries in `backend/docs/ADR_OVERVIEW.md` / `ADR_FEATURES.md` (per team practice).

## Commits and PRs

- Commit messages: **imperative mood**, concise subject; body explains *why* when non-obvious.
- PR description: **what** changed, **how to verify** (tests, manual steps), migration/deploy notes if any.
